    "In order to further investigate this assumption, isorate curves were obtained similarly to G-PCC, i.e., searching the value for gqp that keeps the same or lower bitrate as the CTC configurations for different aqp values.",
    "The corresponding results can be observed in Fig. 5.",
    "In this analysis, the occupancyPrecision was again kept at a value of 4.The isorate plots from Fig. 5 further indicate that the configurations present in the CTC document provide good performance, always achieving the optimal or near-optimal PCQM value for its rate across the evaluated samples.",
    "A small increment in aqp leads sometimes to improved PCQM values, but is followed by a decline when the variation is large.",
    "On the other hand, decreasing aqp leads to a sharp decline in quality in some cases."
